org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.process.traversal

Interface Parameterizing

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddEdgeStep, AddPropertyStep, AddVertexStartStep, AddVertexStep

    public interface Parameterizing
    An interface for Step implementations that hold a Parameters object, which fold in arguments from other steps. It is typically used on mutating steps, such as addV(), where calls to property(k,v) are folded in as parameters to that add vertex step.
    Author:
    Marko A. Rodriguez (http://markorodriguez.com), Stephen Mallette (http://stephen.genoprime.com)
